	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Mid day news bits from Lady Dae</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=232637" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/harpys-head/Forum9/HTML/000040.html">Test of Tactics - Best of the Best</a></B><P>

<I>Verant Interactive Presents<BR>
The Test of Tactics – Best of the Best Event<P>

The Test of Tactics was the first official event held by Verant Interactive, being held over a year ago on Xegony. The event is designed as a 6 vs 6 event, with minimal amounts of rules involved. Due to the massive time cost on the event, it was decided upon to move to smaller events that would take less time to run and place a smaller burden on the server staff.<P>

With the incredible demand that the players have shown for the events, we are going to bring back the Test of Tactics, and do a Best of the Best for all servers to find the greatest 6-man team. We have modified the rules slightly so that we don’t have 200 teams per server enter, and it will be able to be run quickly and efficiently, while still trying to keep the original spirit of the event alive.<P>

The 6-man team has now become a 7-man team. The “Captain” of the team must be a level 58 or higher. Two “Elite” team members need to be 55 or higher. The final 4 of the team make up 3 “Support” team members of 49th level plus, and a “Substitute/Coach” position that can be of any level. This does allow for a 7-man team of all 60th level players.<P>

Only 6 will fight at one time, and the 7th can be substituted before the match. Once the team has been chosen, those 6 must fight. The 7th during the match is restricted to observation or coaching.<P>

Rules are fairly simple. No starting buffs, no starting pets, no use of fear, no use of charm, and no use of knock back spells. Once the match starts, you may buff, summon pets, use activatable items, cast spells, engage with melee, hide and sneak, disarm opponents, use uber-quest weapons, do whatever is needed to assure the victory of your team.<P>

The “Ring” for this match is the raised platform of the arena. The only characters allowed in the center arena is the 12 players involved, and the Lead Judge of the event. All players involved must remain in the tiles at all times. Leaving the tiles for any reason will result in a warning, then disqualification of the player involved.<P>

Security for this event will be extreme. Any non-combatant who even stands up on the raised platform will be removed from the arena and banished from the event. No spell casting, no bard song, no use of shout will be tolerated at anytime for those watching the event. Event Staff can and will remove any player that causes even the slightest disruption of this massive event.<P> 

Before the claims of uber-guild, uber-item, uber-whatever start, be advised that of the 3 Test of Tactics that have been held, the team that has practiced the most have won these events, even over higher levels, better equipped, and longer playing characters. How well you understand the basics of 6 vs 6 player vs player combat, and getting a well balanced team will determine how well your group does in the event.<P>

The ToT-BotB will start October 16th and run through October 28th on Live Servers. The final event will be a 2-day event on Test Server, October 28th and 29th.<P>

Prizes for this incredible event are still undecided, as well as the question of an entry fee. This will be discussed and made final in the next week.<P>

Good luck to everyone participating, I shall see you on the battlefields!<P>

Lady Daegarmo<BR>
Online Events Coordinator<BR>
Verant Interactive</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/harpys-head/Forum9/HTML/000041.html">"Minor" Events</a></B><P>

<I>Be advised that we are busy prepairing for the "Minor" events that are designed for levels 1 to 54.<P>

I am awaiting word from the different servers on when and which events will be held, and will be presenting a list here shortly. The events will be server only, and not move to a final on test.<P>

Should know more in the next day or two! <P>

At this time, there will be an entry fee (Level times Level in Gold) and the prize will be winner takes all coin.<P>

Good luck to everyone!<P>

Lady Dae</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/harpys-head/Forum9/HTML/000038.html">yay!</a></B><P>

I'm pretty sure that the contest here will have something to do with healing (what a surprise!)What we will be healing is the real question. Best clerics out there are the ones that save the enchanter that is getting pounded when he's at only a few hp away from death (save the enchanter, save the whole group). My only advice here is to get your alteration up, and if you haven't specialized in that, well, it's time to do that lil quest in the temple of solusek!<P>

<B>The next major event will be the Test of Tactics in late October, followed by the Wizards - Best of the Best in mid-November.<P>

The soonest we would be seeing a cleric - Best of the Best would be Early December, and that all depends on luck of the roll. =)<P>

I am sure by then we will have a great event planned for the clerics.<P>

Lady Dae</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/harpys-head/Forum9/HTML/000018.html">Events</a></B><P>

Even some people in the US could not make it to some of those event times used for the recent rogue tournament. I saw one event scheduled for 2pm PST. Most people in the US would be at work at that time! In fact, the earliest that an event should be held for US people is 7pm PST. That should allow sufficent time to get home and have something to eat at least.<P>

Better, yet, stop holding them during the week, and just do them on weekends.<P>

<B>When it comes to the best of the best series, I have 35 or so servers now that I have to have champions to represent each server.<P>

It is hard enough for me to be in 4 places at one time, can you imagine trying to do 35 of these events in a day or two? Eeep!<P>

I wish that I had that kind of staff to be able to do these kinds of events, but for now, the max that I can do is about 4 to 5 a day. That means I have to run them on the weekdays.<P>

I will make every attempt at schedueling some minor events on the off hours so that many non-USA players can at least attend those.<P>

My appologies, I promise that I will do what I can to get these events to as many players as possible.<P>

Lady Daegarmo</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/harpys-head/Forum9/HTML/000020.html">arena fighting is a joke!</a></B><P>

If GM run events are so "Protected" can you explain the GM event in "NAJENA" about 2 months ago. Najena is listed as a 12 - 30 zone. <P>

<B>Please see the post "The difference between Events and Quest"<P>

Those that are stating no "protection" are talking about Quests, not Events<P>

Lady Daegarmo</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
